-- Colombia Stocks: Bancolombia, Grupo de Inversiones Suramericana
-- B y   A n d r e a   J a r a m i l l o
-- 2012-01-06T21:22:42Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-06/colombia-stocks-bancolombia-grupo-de-inversiones-suramericana.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4 p.m. local time.  The  IGBC Index (IGBC)  fell 0.3 percent to 12,932.56, while the
Colcap Index dropped 0.4 percent to 1,599.69.  Bancolombia SA (PFBCOLO)  (PFBCOLO CB),  Colombia ’s biggest lender,
fell 3.2 percent to 27,300 pesos, a six-week low, after the
company said it plans to raise as much as 1.66 trillion pesos
$882 million) in a share sale starting today. The Medellin-based
lender will offer to sell 64 million non-voting preferred shares
at 26,000 pesos each to current shareholders between today and
Jan. 27, it said in a statement late yesterday. Shares that
aren’t sold in Colombia will be offered abroad as level 3
American depositary receipts, according to the statement.  Grupo de Inversiones Suramericana SA (GRUPOSUR)  , the
parent company of Bancolombia, rose 0.3 percent to 32,400 pesos.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andrea Jaramillo in Bogota at 
